quran[51]{c,v,t}:
  26,1,"Ta, Sin, Mim. (These are the names of letters of Arabic alphabet, and only Allah knows their meaning here)"
  26,2,"Those (Literally: that). are the ayat (Verses, signs) of the evident Book"
  26,3,You would possibly consume yourself that they are not believers
  26,4,"In case We (so) decide, We will be sending down on them from the heaven a sign so their necks linger subdued to it"
  26,5,And in no way does a recent Remembrance come up to them from The All-Merciful except they are veering away from it
  26,6,Then they have readily cried lies; so the tidings will soon come up to them of what they used to mock at
  26,7,"And have they not regarded the earth, how many therein We have caused to grow of every honorable pair"
  26,8,Surely in that is indeed a sign; and in no way were most of them believers
  26,9,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,10,"And as your Lord called out to Musa, (Moses) (saying), \"Come up to the unjust people"
  26,11,The people of Firaawn. (Pharaoh) Will they not be pious
  26,12,"He said, \"Lord! Surely I fear they will cry me lies"
  26,13,"And my breast will be straitened, and my tongue will not be free. (i.e., it will not express well; literally, will not go off freely) So send to Harun. (Aaron)"
  26,14,And they have a guilty deed against me; so I fear they will kill me
  26,15,"Said He, \"Not at all, so go (both of you) with Our signs; surely We will be with you, listening"
  26,16,"So come up to Firaawn, then say (to him), \"We (both) are the Messenger of The Lord of the worlds"
  26,17,"(Saying) Send forth with us the Seeds (Or: sons) of .\" Israel"
  26,18,"Said he, \"Did we not rear you among us as a newborn, and did you not linger among us years of your age"
  26,19,And you performed the performance you performed and you were one of the disbelievers
  26,20,"He (Musa) (Moses) said, \"lo, I performed it and I was of the erring"
  26,21,So I fled from you as soon as I feared you. Then my Lord bestowed upon me judgment and He made me one of the Emissaries
  26,22,"And is that a favor you oblige me with, that you have taken the Seeds (Or: sons) of Israel) as slaves"
  26,23,"Firaawn (Pharaoh) said, \"And what is The Lord of the worlds"
  26,24,"He said, \"The Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them (both), in case you have certitude"
  26,25,"He said to the ones around him, \"Do you not listen"
  26,26,"He said, \"Your Lord and The Lord of your earliest fathers"
  26,27,"He said, \"Surely your Messenger who has been sent to you is indeed a madman"
  26,28,"He said, \"The Lord of the east and the west and whatever is between them (both), in case you (can) consider"
  26,29,"He said, \"Indeed in case you take to yourself a god other than me, indeed I will definitely make you one of the imprisoned"
  26,30,"He said, \"Even if I come to you with (some) thing evident"
  26,31,"He said, \"Come up with it then, in case you are of the sincere ones"
  26,32,"So he cast his staff, then, only then was it a (demonstrably) evident serpent"
  26,33,"And he drew out his hand, then, only then was it white to the onlookers"
  26,34,"He (Firaawn) said to the chiefs around him, \"Surely this is indeed a knowledgeable sorcerer"
  26,35,Who would like to drive you out of your land by his sorcery; so what do you command
  26,36,"They said, \"Put him off, (him) and his brother, and send forth into the cities musterers"
  26,37,"Who will come up to you with every crafty, knowledgeable sorcerer"
  26,38,So the sorcerers were gathered (together) for the fixed time on a known day. (A day of festival)
  26,39,"And it was said to the citizens, \"Will you be gathered (together)"
  26,40,"That possibly we would closely follow the sorcerers, in case they are the ones who are the overcomers"
  26,41,"Then, when the sorcerers came, they said to Firaawn, (Pharaoh) \"will we surely have a reward indeed, in case we are the ones who are the overcomers"
  26,42,"He said, \"Yes, and lo indeed, surely you will be indeed among the near-stationed"
  26,43,"Musa (Moses) said to them, \"Cast you down whatever you will be casting"
  26,44,"So they cast down their ropes and their staffs and said, \"By the might of Firaawn, we, surely we, will indeed be the overcomers"
  26,45,"Then Musa cast down his staff, then, only then did it gulp whatever falshood they (showed)"
  26,46,"So the sorcerers were cast down, prostrating themselves"
  26,47,"They said, \"We believe in The Lord of the worlds"
  26,48,"The Lord of Musa and Harun.\" (Aaron)"
  26,49,"He (Firaawn) said, \"You have believed him before I give you permission. Surely he is indeed your great (master) who taught you sorcery. Yet indeed you will eventually know! Indeed I will definitely cut off (The form of the verb implies something done repeatedly, or to a high degree or great extent. (cf. surat yusuf 3 1) your hands and legs alternately, and indeed I will definitely crucify you all together"
  26,50,"They said, \"It is no trouble; surely to our Lord we are turning back. (Literally: turning over)"
  26,51,"Surely we long for (the fact) that our Lord should forgive us our sins, for that we are the first of the believers"